            <abstract id="ref2" label="Abstract">This collection consists of various ephemera relating to Brooklyn, donated to the Brooklyn Historical Society by Clark S. Marlor. Items include programs, a calendar, greeting and note cards, and pages from issues of 
                <emph render="italic">Harper's Weekly</emph> from the 1860s containing images and information of significance to Brooklyn history. Also included are records of expenses for the funeral of Z.H. Zerbe.</abstract>
